"```sql\nSELECT AVG(bond_count) AS average_bonds_per_iodine_atom\nFROM (\n    SELECT a.atom_id, COUNT(b.bond_id) AS bond_count\n    FROM atom a\n    JOIN connected c ON a.atom_id = c.atom_id\n    JOIN bond b ON c.bond_id = b.bond_id\n    WHERE a.element = 'i'\n    GROUP BY a.atom_id\n) AS iodine_atom_bonds;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the average number of bonds for atoms with the element iodine. It first counts the number of bonds for each iodine atom and then computes the average of these counts."